criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. the people who understand and would sign the informed consent voluntarily;

          2. Aged 18 to 80 years old;

          3. hospitalized patients diagnosed as acute coronary syndrome in the past 1 months;

               1. hsCRP > 2mg/L;

               2. allopurinol allergy gene HLA-B5801 was negative.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. history of coronary artery bypass grafting;

          2. allergy to allopurinol or any excipient;

          3. administration of allopurinol or other uric-acid-lowering drugs within 7 days before
             randomization;

          4. abnormal liver function (ALT >1.5 fold of the upper limit);

          5. renal dysfunction (creatinine clearance rate <45 ml/min);

          6. thrombocytopenia (PLT<100g/L);

          7. gout patients;

          8. uncontrolled infectious diseases in screening period;

          9. Thyroid dysfunction, moderate to severe anemia (hemoglobin < 90g/L), systemic lupus
             erythematosus, malignant hematopathy, leukopenia, asthma, inflammatory bowel disease
             and other immune diseases were found during the screening period;

         10. Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs, steroid hormone, immunomodulatory and
             chemotherapeutic drugs not included in the study protocol should be taken for a long
             time during the study period;

         11. the history of surgery or interventional operation within 6 months before the
             screening period;

         12. patients with mental disorders such as anxiety or depression;

         13. pregnant women, lactating women or women of childbearing age who did not use effective
             contraceptive measures ;

         14. patients who participated in other clinical trials 3 months before the screening
             period;

         15. the researchers judged that patients were not suitable for this clinical trials.
